#!/usr/bin/env bash

lord -w -x @repo --verbose << "EOF"
Use the bin/lord man page from `man lord` to write a series of tests for the
lord command. The tests shouldn't try to do asserts, they should just be shell
one liners with a certain expected output, and then they should print both.
Keep it simple. And if possible, figure out the right way to make the codex calls so
that the tests run quickly and without using up an unnecessarily large number of tokens,
and add support to bin/lord for changing the amount of 'thinking' or 'effort'
requested from codex exec. I want to be able to make speed vs accuracy tradeoffs
on the command line by passing in well named parameters.
EOF
